content:
Digital Currency Group founder and CEO Barry Silbert updated shareholders on Tuesday and said the company would come out of the current environment stronger a day after media reports that its Genesis unit faced a possible bankruptcy.&nbsp;<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
"DCG will continue to be a leading builder of the industry and we are committed to our long-term mission of accelerating the development of a better financial system," he wrote in a note to clients obtained by The Block. "We have weathered previous crypto winters and while this one may feel more severe, collectively we will come out of it stronger."&nbsp;
